  "prompt": "Is there any way to insert image/picture in nedit text editor?",
  "response": "NEdit, the Nirvana Editor, is primarily a text editor, designed mainly for editing plain text and coding. It does not support inserting images or handling any kind of multimedia content directly within the editor itself. NEdit focuses on providing a robust and efficient environment for writing and editing text and code, but it lacks features for handling non-text elements like images.\n\nIf you need to include images in documents, you might want to consider using a word processing tool or a more fully-featured IDE or document editor that supports multimedia elements. Alternatively, you can keep the images in separate files and reference them from your text documents if you are working with formats like HTML or Markdown that allow linking images from their paths.",
